      • getModeNames

        public StructuredQName[] getModeNames()
                               throws XPathException
        Return the list of mode names to which this template rule is applicable.
        Returns:
        the list of mode names. If the mode attribute is absent, #default is assumed. If #default is present explicitly or implicitly, it is replaced by the default mode, taken from the in-scope default-modes attribute, which defaults to #unnamed. The unnamed mode is represented by Mode.UNNAMED_MODE_NAME. The token #all translates to Mode.OMNI_MODE.
        Throws:
        XPathException - if the attribute is invalid.
